:3;s:46:"Doing so will help to keep the chair in place.";i:4;s:73:"Stand perpendicular to the wall facing the side of the chair as pictured.";i:5;s:26:"Come to standing Tadasana.";i:6;s:26:"Chair Yoga Twist k bonura.";i:7;s:176:"From your seated position gently twist at the waist toward the right bringing your right hand back to the side of the chair and your left hand to the outside of your right leg.";i:8;s:42:"Keep your neck soft with a gentle stretch.";i:9;s:25:"Hold for 5 to 10 breaths.";i:10;s:25:"Repeat on the other side.";i:11;s:113:"Chair Seated Twists included in chair yoga poses is a twist that engages the spine upper back hips neck and arms.";i:12;s:127:"Included in Chair Yoga Sequences as part of warm-up flow the twist helps in better flexibility of the spine shoulders and hips.";i:13;s:92:"It also keeps the joints active which indeed will be helpful when introduced in senior yoga.";i:14;s:53:"Chair Seated Twists practice is a safe way to target.";i:15;s:98:"Revolved utkatasana is a powerful pose that requires a strong legs stable hips and a mobile spine.";i:16;s:66:"This twisting chair yoga sequence prepares the body for such work.";i:17;s:100:"The end result is more space in the tissue efficiency in body communication and clarity in the mind.";i:18;s:75:"These factors combine to release old patterns and make way for your better.";i:19;s:15:"6 Side twist A.";i:20;s:22:"Sit tall in the chair.";i:21;s:101:"Place put your left hand on the seat behind you and your right hand on the outside of your left knee.";i:22;s:61:"Inhale and reach your head up with energy toward the ceiling.";i:23;s:53:"As you exhale gently turn your shoulders to the left.";i:24;s:78:"To help deepen your twist gently press your left hand against your right knee.";i:25;s:70:"Yoga twists are so fun to practice and theyre really good for you too.";i:26;s:127:"As you practice your spinal twists youre nourishing the health and flexibility of your spine and refreshing all of your organs.";i:27;s:95:"This article will walk you through nine yoga poses for spinal twists from beginner to advanced.";i:28;s:83:"Exhale Twist this little trick should be applied to all seated and standing twists.";i:29;s:67:"Inhale and lengthen the spine first before exhaling into the twist.";i:30;s:113:"Pause Breathe - pausing in seated and supine twists will help to release tension around the spine and lower back.";i:31;s:69:"Even as you pause continue this pattern with the breath and movement.";i:32;s:47:"Inhale to lengthen more exhale to twist deeper.";i:33;s:30:"12 Yoga Chair Pose With Twist.";i:34;s:82:"Check out our yoga therapy section to learn which yogic practices have been shown.";i:35;s:147:"Chair seated twist pose benefits the following muscles and hence can be included in yoga sequences with the corresponding muscles focus 5 Steps to.";i:36;s:171:"The Seated Chair Twist Im writing about today is one of multiple twists that can be done from a chair but today well be using the back of the chair to assist in the twist.";i:37;s:178:"The Seated Chair Twist helps increase flexibility in the spine and back muscles also stretching the shoulders and chest while building strength and massaging the internal organs.";i:38;s:19:"3 FREE Yoga Videos.";i:39;s:118:"Hi Lovely Sign up here to receive 3 FREE Yoga videos and Ill immediately send you an email with your first yoga video.";i:40;s:139:"This video series is totally free and exclusive to my newsletter subscribers so keep your eyes peeled for my emails over the next few days.";i:41;s:73:"Chair yoga is a form of yoga that has been adapted from traditional yoga.";i:42;s:140:"Typically chair yoga is practiced sitting on a chair or using a chair for support yet still allows for twists stretches and minor backbends.";i:43;s:191:"Chair yoga is ideal for those who might not be able to take part in traditional yoga due to mobility restrictions an injury or those who simply dont have the space to lay down a yoga mat and.";i:44;s:60:"In this chair yoga and breathing class we focus on the hips.";i:45;s:67:"Dont worry we wont forget about neck and shoulders lats and twists.";i:46;s:119:"Lengthen the sides of the trunk as you move your back ribs in and up in a circular motion towards the upper front ribs.";i:47;s:118:"Breathe 4-6 breaths continuing to extend the spine on the inhales and to twist deeper into the posture on the exhales.";i:48;s:68:"Come back and change sides shifting the right hip to the chair back.";i:49;s:25:"Repeat on the other side.";i:50;s:135:"Yoga Therapeutics Yoga Therapy is the use of yoga postures meditation and pranayama to help the body naturally heal and balance itself.";i:51;s:130:"Check out our Yoga Therapy section to learn which yogic practices have been shown to have healing qualities for common complaints.";i:52;s:17:"See also Work It.";i:53;s:51:"If twisting is hard for you or your back is tender.";i:54;s:99:"TRY separating your feet hip-width apart and putting a block on its highest side between your feet.";i:55;s:64:"Press into the block with your bottom hand and stretch your top.";i:56;s:178:"This is one of the most universal twisting poses since it can be used at practically any point during the day both during your yoga practice and while youre going about your day.";i:57;s:213:"For example seated chair twists come in very handy if you work at an office and spend most of your time sitting at the desk seen as they help relieve any tension that has built up in your spine neck and shoulders.";i:58;s:57:"Keep your weight in your heels especially your left heel.";i:59;s:63:"Draw your left thighbone back to keep your hips and knees even.";i:60;s:87:"Then gently roll your belly chest neck and head even more to the right twisting deeper.";i:61;s:124:"Open your arms wide into a straight line pressing your left arm against your right thigh leveraging your twist a bit deeper.";i:62;s:50:"Twists are also often variations on regular poses.";i:63;s:243:"Like Parivrtta Utkatasana Twisted Chair Pose and Parivrtta Trikonasana Revolved Triangle Pose Reclining twist In reclining twists the upper body is stabilized and so most of the twist happens in the lower spine by rotating the pelvis and legs.";i:64;s:20:"REVOLVED CHAIR POSE.";i:65;s:34:"Keep both knees in the same plane.";i:66;s:72:"This is the easiest way to assure that your hips are fixed not rotating.";i:67;s:114:"And thats how I like to use my twists in yoga too I usually teach twists as repetitive movement not as held poses.";i:68;s:81:"In my view the only reason to teach a student to rotate the pelvis on the femurs.";}}